The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, Jan. 22 (PTI): The Centre should disclose details of gifts received from foreign countries by the President, Prime Minister, judges and chiefs of the armed forces, the Central Information Commission has said.           An RTI activist had sought information whether VIPs in the government received gifts in their official or personal capacity and if they kept them in their custody.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): The Maharashtra government on Thursday filed an appeal in the Supreme Court against a decision of Bombay High Court allowing the screening of the film Deshdrohi. The government said the film, allegedly based on the recent hate campaign against North Indians, could trigger violence.                  
	 London (PTI): A man of Indian origin who murdered his two children and tried to commit suicide last year has been sentenced to at least 21 years in jail. Ashok Kalyanjee, 46, had slit the throats of Paul, 6, and Jay, 2, in his car and then tried to set the vehicle, with himself and the boys, on fire.                   
	 Bangalore (PTI): A youth who had allegedly murdered his wifes former boss has been arrested, police said on Thursday. Santhosh told the police Palani, the proprietor of a firm, had allegedly made sexual advances to his wife even after she quit the job.                   
	 Kathmandu (PTI): Nepal will soon appoint a new ambassador to India to replace Durgesh Man Singh who was recalled last year after the Maoists assumed power, foreign minister Upendra Yadav said. Officials said a pro-Maoist candidate was being considered.                  
	 Chennai (PTI): Five unclaimed suitcases at the Chennai airport on Thursday triggered a bomb scare. Officials said the suitcases were found at apron 34 from where a Colombo-bound Jet Airways had taken off. The suitcases contained clothes, the officials said.
                                                                                                                           
